        <bioghist>
            <p>Former newspaper reporter who came to Buffalo in 1907. Served as executive secretary on Buffalo Commission Charter campaign in 1914; held various posts in Republican city administrations of mayors Roesch and Dowd, including budget director, 1930-1934; from 1930 to 1937 was secretary of the N.Y. State Commission for the Revision of the Tax Laws.</p>
        </bioghist>
        
        <scopecontent>
            <p>Transcripts of hearings held in Mayor Louis P. Fuhrmann's office for Commission Charter, 1914; transcripts of committee meetings, draft speeches, memoranda, messages and other papers of Mayor Charles E. Roesch, 1930-1934; and papers of the New York State Commission for the Revision of the Tax laws, including transcripts of public hearings and executive sessions, 1930-1931.</p>
        <arrangement>
                <p>Organized into three series: I. Commission Government Charter transcripts, 1914. II. Papers of Mayor Charles E. Roesch administration, 1930-1934. III. New York State Commission for the Revision of the Tax Laws, 1930-1935. Chronological arrangement within series.</p>
            </arrangement>
        </scopecontent>
